By far the best app for early learning of letter recognition, sound association, and beginning of writing basics and sight words that I have found. My 4 year old learns faster with this app than she ever did using ABCMouse.

It is a good app. It would be nice if the voice recording feature improved, coz i can't really tell when is it recording. Also, letter tracing using finger is not commonly used in smartphone yet, so i think it is hard to do for a kid.

Nice game, bit slow and repetitive. But good practice for little ones learning to read...

Excellent. Engaged my almost 3 year old from the start. Educational in all the right places, coupled with fun graphics and sounds. Entertaining games that offer good practise of phonetics, spelling etc. Recommended.

One of the best reading apps I've tried with my kids for learning to read, would certainly recommend it. Only bit that doesn't seem to make sense to them is the drag your finger and read out loud, even after explaining it seems to be confusing, otherwise that's just 1 part of an excellent game.
Very educational, my 3 year old loves this app! Deserves 10 stars!

I just bought this app for my son and he loves it! This was the most 
absorbed I have seen him in any reading activity. His favorite aspect is 
recording his voice and hearing himself. My son is not very interested in 
video games, but everything about this app is very engaging for him. His 
friend had it on iPad and my son was really excited about it. I was 
surprised to realize that I happened to look for it on the very day it was 
launched here. My son has progressed very quickly so I hope Vol. 2 comes 
out soon.
